Thick plumes of black smoke filled the air after a fuel tanker set alight on a busy road in south Essex this evening. The A130 Canvey Way has been closed at Sadlers Farm due to the inferno, with traffic expected to be affected for some time. Firefighters said the tanker was carrying was carrying around 38,000 litres of aviation fuel. It is still not clear what triggered the blaze or whether anyone has been left injured. Locals are being told to keep their windows and doors closed as smoke wafts through their neighbourhood. Helen Davis, who is stuck in traffic, told the Echo she saw five fire engines and that police were telling drivers to turn around. Eyewitnesses said they could see the smoke rising into the sky roughly 11 miles way from Southend Pier. Describing it as an ‘absolutely horrendous sight’, Courtney Christina Andre said: ‘I hope no one is hurt, it looks very aggressive, and the smoke seems never ending!’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.